{
    "analysis": "We computed global P95 thresholds for the candidate services' metric KPIs using the full metric series, then filtered the incident window and found multiple anomalies. The most severe metric anomaly by far is ts-order-service.diskio (severity_ratio ~149) with earliest anomaly at 1705934400. Several services (ts-train-service, ts-route-service, ts-travel-service, ts-auth-service) show latency spikes (latency-50 and latency-90) with severity ratios from ~1.05 up to ~5.3. According to the diagnosis workflow, multiple service-level faults are present; to localize the root-cause component we must inspect traces to determine call relationships and identify the most downstream faulty service within affected traces. Trace analysis should use global thresholds (e.g., global P95) computed on full trace series first, then detect anomalies in the incident window and highlight traces involving the candidate services (trace names containing ts-order-service, ts-train-service, ts-route-service, ts-travel-service, ts-auth-service). This will tell us which faulty service appears downstream in the problematic call chains and help pick the root cause.",
